<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef9f79c5-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302501"><num value="302501">§ 302501.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f79c6-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302501/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Designation</inline>.—</heading><content>The term “designation” means the identification and registration of property for protection that meets criteria established by a State or locality for significant historic property within the jurisdiction of a local government.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f79c7-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302501/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Protection</inline>.—</heading><content>The term “protection” means protection by means of a local review process under State or local law for proposed demolition of, changes to, or other action that may affect historic property designated pursuant to this chapter.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idef9f79c8-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3197">128 Stat. 3197</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
